.cs 3 on
.item 'CENTER Command' 'Updated on 04/15/83 by EAB'
.boxon
CENTER range [LENGTH=n] [AROUND=n] [INDENT=n] [list-options]
.*     <---> <--------> <--------> <--------> <------------>
.* FIELD COMMAND HELP CENTER range
.* FIELD COMMAND HELP CENTER LENGTH
.* FIELD COMMAND HELP CENTER AROUND
.* FIELD COMMAND HELP CENTER INDENT
.* FIELD COMMAND HELP CENTER list-options
.boxoff

.* DESCRIPTION
The CENTER command centers each line of text in the range within the length
specified.  If you do not specify a length, WYLBUR uses the global length.
(Type HELP SET LENGTH for description of length.)\

.* SELECT 'CENTER Command Options'
.us Option Descriptions

.* OPTION RANGE
.optix range
range\\\\\\\\\\\is the range of lines to be centered.  This option is required
                and must be specified first.  (Type HELP RANGE for a
                description of range.)\

.* OPTION LENGTH
.optix LENGTH
LENGTH=n\\\\\\\\specifies the line length within which the contents of each
                line is to be centered; n may be any value from 1 to 235.  The
                default value is the global length.  (Type HELP SET LENGTH for
                a description of length.)\

.* OPTION AROUND
.optix AROUND
AROUND=n\\\\\\\\specifies that the text be centered around the specified
                column (n).

.* OPTION INDENT
.optix INDENT
INDENT=n\\\\\\\\allows centering based on a column indentation value; n may be
                any value from 1 to 234.

.* OPTION LIST-OPTIONS,LIST,NOLIST,NOTEXT,NUMBERED,UNNUMBERED,NONUMBERED,INTEGER
.optix list-options
list-options\\\\The list option LIST, specifies that the line be listed after
                it is centered.  NOLIST is the default for this command.  For
                additional list-options, type HELP LIST-OPTIONS.
.cs 3 off
